# api.http - one runnable HTTP request per endpoint of our application.
# Format: the "REST Client" plain-text format. In VS Code install the extension
# named "REST Client" (by Huachao Mao) and a "Send Request" link appears above
# each request; IntelliJ IDEA Ultimate has this built in (Community: use the
# browser or curl for now). Each request block is separated by a ### line.
#
# The app has NO endpoints yet - no code claims any URL. This first request
# exists to PROVE the server is alive: it asks for "/" and the correct answer
# is a 404 Not Found error page, which means "server running, URL unclaimed."

### Is the server alive? (expected result: 404 Not Found - that IS the success signal for now)
GET http://localhost:8080/
